name: Couri Orange Hatchery
overview:
The Couri Hatchery is a student-centered business incubator. Their goal is to promote, stimulate, and support business development within the entrepreneurial student environment at Syracuse University. Business creation at the Couri Hatchery will ultimately lead to the establishment of high-growth companies in New York and nationally. Positive business impacts can only do more to stimulate economic development in the Central New York region and beyond.

The focus of the Couri Hatchery is innovative, emerging student ventures. It provides a broad scope of services including cost-effective space and support, prototype production facilities, product realization and development services, and business consultation.

The Couri Hatchery will stimulate interaction between student entrepreneurs and other Syracuse University students, faculty, administrators, and staff. It will also offer unique research and development collaborations with local entrepreneurs, capitalizing on their facilities, business management expertise, and technologies to leverage our student entrepreneurial success.
